		<p>Savvy Esthetics runs on a strict timely schedule and requires prompt arrival to provide service to all clients. We know there may be times when clients are running late due to emergencies and last-minute delays. That's why we have our late policy. We do this, so all our clients can stay on schedule. Clients who arrive more than 15 minutes late for a scheduled appointment will be charged an additional $25.If you are going to be more than 15 minutes late rescheduling will be required. At 15 minutes, it will limit the amount of time dedicated to the services.</p>
	</div>

	<div>
		<h3>MISSED APPOINTMENT POLICY</h3>
		<p>As a courtesy to clients and the estheticians, appointments must be canceled a minimum of 24 hours in advance. A Venmo Invoice will be sent to you, should the policy not be met. No fee will be charged for appointments that are canceled or rescheduled with at least 24-hour notice. Appointments canceled or rescheduled without a minimum 24 hours-notice will be charged an additional $25 charge. The same fee applies to no-shows. Cancellations and/or rescheduling must be communicated via text message or phone calls.</p>

